IMPACT_FINANCIAL: We are very fortunate, my boyfriend is a teacher so is receiving his full salary and can pay for our flat rent, although it is very expensive. I am living off my student loan so we have not been directly affected as I was not working.
IMPACT_EMOTIONAL: I struggle with severe anxiety, not being able to see my family for almost 2 months now has greatly effected me. My exams this semester have also been cancelled in uni and have been given replacement courseworks which I find more stressful, especially since they are pass/fail and not contributing to my qualification. The uni is not very transparent on what is going to happen with results this year so a very stressful time overall.
IMPACT_PHYSICAL: Due to my anxiety I have struggled to leave the house and exercise as I really don't trust that other people will be following the same guidelines. I fear getting the virus primarily because I don't want to get my boyfriends and my own family ill when the lockdown is alleviated. We are also not having balanced meals as we're trying to space out our shopping as much as possible so we're often having a lot of carbs and protein rather than lots of varied vegetables.
PARTNER_CONTACT_QUAL: Living with them, see each other 24 hours a day at the moment!
RELATIONSHIP_TECH: When we were both out we would only contact each other by a call or messages during the day on a mobile.
RELATIONSHIP_QUAL: General intimacy is obviously a lot greater, we are spending more time together and we're fortunate that we have the same hobbies such as playing games/music/looking after our plants. Our sexual activity is about the same though. There are no obvious negatives in our relationship, sometimes we get a bit irritated over little things more frequently than before.
SOCTECH_TRANSITION: It was fairly easy, I do feel it's a little more awkward and all I'm thinking is I can't wait to see them in person. We've had a couple drinks over facetime and it's good fun but definitely not the same.
SOCTECH_USEFUL_QUAL: We generally just message as our friend group is not really the type to post updates for everyone to see. Sometimes we'll post pictures on snapchat though and it's good to keep up to date with people i'm not directly talking to.
SOCTECH_IMPRESSION_QUAL: Again, I suppose it's good to keep in touch with other people, however I've also seen many taking advantage and flaunting their political agendas and using the situation to attack the tories or promote labour which I feel is unnecessary at the current time. I do see how this is a delicate time for everyone and how people would be critical at the same time though.

IMPACT_FINANCIAL: Significantly. I am currently furloughed with the prospect of not having a job to go back to.
IMPACT_EMOTIONAL: Again, significantly. Ups and downs, but both the ups and downs seem to be higher. Definitely enjoying having the pace of my life slowed down a little though (no international travel for work is a huge bonus to me mentally and my stress levels are so much lower!)
IMPACT_PHYSICAL: I'm doing less exercise, but still keeping up with some. I used to be in the gym on a strict weightlifting programme 5-6 days a week and obviously that is no longer possible. So I am feeling the effects of not exercising as much.
PARTNER_CONTACT_QUAL: We live in a small, 1 bedroom flat so contact is definitely not a problem! Having some space to yourself is more of the problem.
RELATIONSHIP_TECH: For the first year of our relationship we were 1200 miles apart so technology was massive. Now a lot less so, and especially in lockdown we only use it when one of us is out.
RELATIONSHIP_QUAL: I'd say that at the start (early days of lockdown) we were both a bit stressed about the situation so our intimate relationship was not good. Now we've settled in and have more time with each other, we're both less tired, have fewer social commitments and have found that our intimate relationship has definitely improved. We're enjoying spending more time together, for sure.
SOCTECH_TRANSITION: It's not been that hard for me as I work in a digital agency that uses online communication a lot day to day. However, for people like my parents and non-techy friends I think it's been a bit more stressful as the whole process isn't always seamless. I've found myself tiring of video calls (we're calling it Zoom fatigue) much faster than I would talking to these people in person.
SOCTECH_USEFUL_QUAL: Keeping in touch with people I usually see most days. Also for getting a general feel of the attitude towards the pandemic from my social circle, with has been interesting to say the least
SOCTECH_NEWS_QUAL: I follow a number of media outlets (BBC, Buzzfeed, The Independent, The Guardian) and see the posts in my timeline
SOCTECH_IMPRESSION_QUAL: I think they're good for making you feel like you're connected to others, but it's all a bit false to me as so much content on social media is heavily edited (idea of only showing your 'best life' on there which just isn't accurate 99% of the time). I do think that aspect of social media can be very dangerous, especially to young people.
PORN_CHANGE_QUAL: Well, just more free time I guess! Also started watching it with my partner (not something we ever did before) which has been fun
PORN_CHANGE_WHICH: I watch for longer,I watch porn when bored,I watch porn with my partner
SEX_HEALTH_QUAL: My partner and I are monogamous, and were each tested when we got together 4 years ago. I wouldn't feel the need to be tested again now unless we broke up and got new partners or opened our relationship

IMPACT_FINANCIAL: I wasn't able to get a job after graduating from college (I wanted to start working in the service industry in March) and now I am fully financially dependent on my family. My graduate scheme which should be starting in July might also get postponed because of COVID-19 which means I would be stuck without any income for even longer.
IMPACT_EMOTIONAL: I do feel anxious about the future a lot and it is really frustrating to have to put my life on hold just as it was finally starting to get better (I graduated university, was offered my ultimate dream job for an amazing company). I also often feel angry and defeated by the lack of information from the government and by the lack of action in the beginning of the pandemic which now caused us to be stuck in lockdown while many other countries are ready to reopen.
IMPACT_PHYSICAL: I honestly feel quite a bit better physically than I did before the lockdown since I have no obligations and not much to do inside the house so I tend to go out almost everyday for long walks. I even started running for the first time in my life and doing yoga. On the other hand, I had some minor health issues that are worrying me but I can't go to the doctor to get help because of the coronavirus situation.
ONLINE_QUAL: I moved to London right before the lockdown started so I literally don't know anyone in this city other than my roommate and the lockdown made it seem even more lonely and isolating. I am hoping to connect with some people on these sites and hopefully meet some of them after the lockdown is over. I usually get quite anxious about going on dates with people I met online/do not know, but after being stuck at home for so long I feel much more excited about doing so.
SOCTECH_TRANSITION: It is nice to have the opportunity to still see my friends and talk to them but it is definitely not the same as being able to see them in person. It's really hard to find a time for a skype call when everyone is available, there are almost always some technical issues and it's not the same as being able to bond over doing some activities together, eating out etc.
SOCTECH_USEFUL_QUAL: I am able to see what my friends are doing, for example by looking at their instagram stories, or send them messages and share content with them, which makes me feel at least a little bit more connected to them. It also helps to see that we are all struggling with the same things and have that shared experience.
SOCTECH_IMPRESSION_QUAL: I feel there are very useful in providing a space where you can connect with your friends and other people, get inspiration for activities that can be done in the lockdown etc. but some social networking sites have also been extensively used to spread misinformation and conspiracy theories during the crisis.
PORN_CHANGE_QUAL: It is difficult to compare since some of my circumstances changed since the lockdown. I used to live alone and now I live with four roommates that are always home so I don't have that much privacy. Overall, I feel like some weeks I watch pornography more than before because of the feelings of isolation from real people and then there are weeks where I watch it a lot less than before because I don't really feel in the right mood for sex as a result of all the anxiety related to the current lockdown situation and the future.
PORN_PARTNER_QUAL: I do not have a partner.
